<Docs title="Harness Adapters">
  <h1>Harness</h1>
  <p class="lead">A harness is the coding agent that runs your repo — Claude Code today; Codex and Cursor soon. The harness adapter compiles your .life into the files that harness expects. Same source, different outputs.</p>

  <h2>What harness adapters do</h2>
  <p>Each harness adapter is a gene the engine loads (the engine bundles none) — the installer pulls one so the first <code>evolve</code> can compile. Each harness has its own file conventions; the adapter generates them from Life source: the resolved graph of every cell's <code>skills:</code>, <code>commands:</code>, <code>surfaces:</code>, <code>hooks:</code>, <code>mcp:</code>, and <code>harness:</code> declarations.</p>
  <p>The output is build output. It is regenerated by <code>life evolve</code> every session and gitignored — editing a generated file is the classic mistake; the fix belongs in the gene or <code>.life</code> that compiles into it.</p>

  <h2>Claude Code</h2>
  <p>The live adapter: <a href="/claude-code"><code>claude-code</code></a>. Compiles into:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>.claude/settings.json</code> — permissions, hook wiring, MCP enable-list. The one <em>tracked</em> harness file, so session-start hooks fire on the very first prompt of a cold clone.</li>
    <li><code>.claude/hooks/</code> — the lifecycle hook scripts each gene declared.</li>
    <li><code>.claude/skills/</code> — skills mounted from genes and local cells.</li>
    <li><code>.claude/commands/</code> + <code>.claude/scripts/</code> — slash commands and helper scripts from <code>surfaces:</code>.</li>
    <li><code>AGENTS.md</code> — the agents.md-convention rendering of the same source.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The session lifecycle</h2>
  <p>A session unfolds in phases, and at each one the compiled hooks run:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>SessionStart</strong> — <code>life evolve</code> brings the genome current, then each gene's start hooks inject what makes the container <em>this</em> .life: the Laws, memory, identity, hydrated secrets.</li>
    <li><strong>UserPromptSubmit / PreToolUse</strong> — per-turn and per-tool hooks (guardrails, leak guards).</li>
    <li><strong>Stop</strong> — push committed work, archive the transcript.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Run <code>life status --lifecycle</code> inside a .life to see the live map — what each gene injects, in which phase, in what order.</p>

  <h2>No fake parity</h2>
  <p>Each adapter declares what it actually supports. If a harness can't support a hook or lifecycle event, that capability is honestly absent rather than emulated. Codex and Cursor adapters will compile the same source to their conventions (<code>AGENTS.md</code>, <code>.cursor/rules/</code>) when they land.</p>
</Docs>
